sync - Flush filesystems


This program acts nearly identical to the Unix command of the same name.
It will tell the specified (or all) Amiga filesystem handlers to flush
dirty data out to disk.

Usage:
	sync [<options>] [<device>...]

Options
	-h display help
	-v verbose mode


When no device is specified on the command line, all filesystem
handlers are told to flush.  Otherwise, only the specified filesystem
will be flushed.  The <device> may be a device or volume name (with colon)
or any filename on that device.

